==English==

===Etymology===
French numismatique, from Late Latin numisma, numismat-, coin, variant of Latin nomisma, from Greek, custom, current coin, from nomizein, to have in use, from nomos, custom.
See nem- in Indo-European Roots.

===Pronunciation===
nmz-mtk, -ms-, ny-

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''numismatics'''
nu·mis·mat·ic    
# The study of [[coin]]s.
